//
// Regression for https://github.com/Xilinx/mlir-aie/issues/2463: cyclostatic
// acquire (hold 3, slide window by 1 per iter) inside an scf.for loop. The
// default dynamic-objFifos lowering currently emits AcquireGreaterEqual(3)
// every iter instead of (1) for iters >= 1, exhausting the producer pool and
// deadlocking. This test will fail (kernel returns ERT_CMD_STATE_TIMEOUT)
// until the lowering subtracts the carried-over held count.
//
// REQUIRES: ryzen_ai_npu2, peano, xrt_python_bindings
//
// RUN: %python %S/aie2.py npu2 > aie.mlir
// RUN: %python aiecc.py --no-aiesim --aie-generate-xclbin --aie-generate-npu-insts --no-compile-host --xclbin-name=aie.xclbin --npu-insts-name=insts.bin ./aie.mlir
// RUN: %run_on_npu2% %python %S/test.py -x aie.xclbin -k MLIR_AIE -i insts.bin
